IP2WHOIS is a free tool to allow you to check WHOIS information for a particular domain, such as domain assigned owner contact information, registrar information, registrant information, location and much more.

To use the IP2WHOIS API, you will need to make a GET request to the `/` endpoint, passing in the domain name for lookup purposes in the `domain` parameter, as well as an API key in the `key` parameter. You can also specify the format of the response in the `format` parameter, with `json` being the default.

Here is an example of how you can use the IP2WHOIS API in your application:
```
GET https://api.ip2whois.com/v2/domain?domain=example.com&key=YOUR_API_KEY&format=json
```
The response will contain information about the domain, including the registrant's contact information, location, and other details.

